items.name: Horilka
items.description: Horilka is a Ukrainian alcoholic beverage. The word horilka may also be used in a generic sense in the Ukrainian language to mean vodka or other strong spirits and etymologically is similar to the Ukrainian word for burning - hority.

items.name: Varenyky
items.description: Varenyky are popular Ukrainian dumplings filled with a variety of ingredients such as vegetables, meat, cheese, sauerkraut, eggs, mushrooms, and even fruit.

items.name: Holubtsi
items.description: Holubtsi are traditional Ukrainian cabbage rolls, especially beloved in the Carpathians.

items.name: Chicken Kyiv
items.description: Chicken Kiev is a dish made of chicken fillet pounded and rolled around cold butter, then coated with eggs and bread crumbs, and either fried or baked.

items.name: Com tam
items.description: Rice with pork, eggs, familiar in Vietnam

items.name: Kvass
items.description: Kvass is a traditional fermented Slavic and Baltic beverage commonly made from rye bread.

items.name: Uzvar
items.description: The uzvar is a national Ukrainian beverage, cooked with dried fruits and berries.

items.name: Sugar cane juice
items.description: If you want a sweet drink, go for it!
